Random walk¶

In [33]:
def random_process(sample_size=200):
    a = 0
    b = 100         #replicate starting point of SPY shown later
    rho = 0.995     #empirically good number
    X, Y = [], []

    aSamples = np.random.normal(size=sample_size)
    bSamples = np.random.normal(size=sample_size)

    for i in range(0, sample_size):
        X.append(i)
        Y.append(a + b)

        a = a * rho + aSamples[i]
        b = b + rho * bSamples[i]
    return X,Y

In [177]:
n = 150
df2 = df.query('date=="2018-06-06"').copy()

df2.iloc[:n].close.diff().describe()
loc = df2.iloc[:n].close.diff().mean()
scale = df2.iloc[:n].close.diff().std()
for i in range(3):
    rands = np.random.normal(loc=loc, scale=scale, size=361-n)
    x = df2.iloc[n].close
    x2 = x+rands.cumsum()#+np.random.normal(size=361-n)
    df3 = pd.DataFrame({
        'real': df2.iloc[n:].close.values,
        'sim': x2}, index=df2.index[n:])
    df3.plot()
    df3['d'] = df3['sim']-df3['real']
